  <source>University Hospitals Cleveland Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Uroxatral (alfuzosin) may not only help BPH symptoms but may also improve sexual function in
      males with BPH and ED.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The study will consist of a 30 day screening/washout phase at the end of which qualified
      subjects will be assigned to alfuzosin 10 mg tablets once a day. Subjects will be treated for
      90 days. The total duration of the study will be 120 days.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
